# .claude/skills/ and .claude/hooks/ are shared, git-worthy tooling and are
# tracked. Everything else under .claude/ is local scratch/config -- a
# blanket `.claude/` ignore can't be selectively un-ignored per-subdir (git
# won't descend into an excluded parent to evaluate negation patterns), so
# the local-only pieces are named explicitly instead.
.claude/work/
.claude/metrics/
.claude/feedback/
.claude/settings.local.json
